170 grams Dried Orzo
250 grams Cherry Tomatoes
2 unit(s) Garlic
1 unit(s) Chilli
50 grams Grated Italian Style Hard Cheese
125 grams Mushrooms
1 sachet(s) Hello Muscat
65 grams Creme Fraiche
5 grams Parsley
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Water
to taste Butter
to taste Oil
to taste Sugar

Peel and grate the garlic (or use a garlic press).
Quarter the mushrooms, halving any larger quarters.
Halve the chilli lengthways. Deseed and finely chop.
Roughly chop the parsley (stalks and all).

Place a large pot over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Once hot, fry the garlic, mushrooms and cherry tomatoes until softened, stirring occasionally, 4-6 mins.

Add the muscat, 400ml water, ½ tsp sugar, ½ tsp salt and 1 tbsp butter (double all for 4p) to the pot.
Stir in half the parsley along with the orzo and chopped chilli (use less if you don't like spice).
Bring to the boil, cover and simmer until the orzo is tender, 15-20 mins.
Stir every 3-4 mins to prevent sticking.
Stir through the creme fraiche and half the cheese then season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide your creamy veggie orzo between bowls.
Top with a scattering of the remaining parsley and grated cheese.